{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idb6a28c42-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s300ff–81"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"300ff–81"},"text":"§ 300ff–81.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Coordination","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idb6a28c43-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s300ff–81/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Requirement","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Secretary shall ensure that the Health Resources and Services Administration, the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention, the Substance Abuse and Mental Health Services Administration, and the Centers for Medicare & Medicaid Services coordinate the planning, funding, and implementation of Federal HIV programs (including all minority AIDS initiatives of the Public Health Service, including under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s300ff–121"},"text":"section 300ff–121 of this title","children":[],"tail":") to enhance the continuity of care and prevention services for individuals with HIV/AIDS or those at risk of such disease. The Secretary shall consult with other Federal agencies, including the Department of Veterans Affairs, as needed and utilize planning information submitted to such agencies by the States and entities eligible for assistance under this subchapter."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idb6a28c44-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s300ff–81/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Report","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Secretary shall biennially prepare and submit to the appropriate committees of the Congress a report concerning the coordination efforts at the Federal, State, and local levels described in this section, including a description of Federal barriers to HIV program integration and a strategy for eliminating such barriers and enhancing the continuity of care and prevention services for individuals with HIV/AIDS or those at risk of such disease.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idb6a28c45-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s300ff–81/c"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"c"},"text":"(c)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Integration by State","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"As a condition of receipt of funds under this subchapter, a State shall provide assurances to the Secretary that health support services funded under this subchapter will be integrated with other such services, that programs will be coordinated with other available programs (including Medicaid), and that the continuity of care and prevention services of individuals with HIV/AIDS is enhanced.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idb6a28c46-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s300ff–81/d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"d"},"text":"(d)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Integration by local or private entities","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"As a condition of receipt of funds under this subchapter, a local government or private nonprofit entity shall provide assurances to the Secretary that services funded under this subchapter will be integrated with other such services, that programs will be coordinated with other available programs (including Medicaid), and that the continuity of care and prevention services of individuals with HIV is enhanced.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idb6a28c47-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1944-07-01/ch373"},"text":"July 1, 1944, ch. 373","children":[],"tail":", title XXVI, § 2681, as added and amended "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/109/415/tV/s501"},"text":"Pub. L. 109–415, title V, § 501","children":[],"tail":", title VII, § 703, "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2006-12-19"},"text":"Dec. 19, 2006","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/120/2812"},"text":"120 Stat. 2812","children":[],"tail":", 2820; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/111/87/s2/a/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 111–87, § 2(a)(1)","children":[],"tail":", (3)(A), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2009-10-30"},"text":"Oct. 30, 2009","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/123/2885"},"text":"123 Stat. 2885","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idb6a28c48-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idb6a28c49-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"priorProvisions","id":"idb6a28c4a-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Prior Provisions","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"A prior section 300ff–81, ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1944-07-01/ch373/tXXVI/s2681"},"text":"act July 1, 1944, ch. 373, title XXVI, § 2681","children":[],"tail":